<a href="#0" id="0">First, we want to understand the nature of correspondence between Wikipedia article edits and discussion page turns.</a>
<a href="#1" id="1">An edit-turn-pair is defined as a pair of an edit from a Wikipedia article ’ s revision history and a turn from the discussion page bound to the same article.</a>
<a href="#2" id="2">The search space for corresponding edit-turn-pairs is quite big, as any edit to an article may correspond to any turn from the article ’ s discussion page.</a>
<a href="#3" id="3">Based on the types of turn and edit in an edit-turn-pair, we have operationalized the notion of corresponding and non-corresponding edit-turn-pairs.</a>
